ll, I guess I will do what many of ya recommended - win some weapon in a group and give that to my Warrior. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ushemmtankdamob.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shemm Tankdamob</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users.surfanytime.co.uk/brian.yeo/crest-sm2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/9/02 4:19:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=435.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Easy Quests Rewarding Weapons?</span><hr size=1> my first quested weapon quest was the BBK, 10/35 1hs. not what you'd call top of the range but it was free.<br><br>i got a sow to sro and then teamed up with a druid/necro/wizzy , basically who-ever was AC hunting. in return for looting the kiliji plans from sandgiant hussam i would sit at zone line and tell them if i saw the AC pop when they were at another part of the zone.<br><br>soemthing to note: i was also allowed to loot pp from dead SG's..but only by wizzy's and necros. those dr00ds are stingy bastards. anyway, this helped to pay for the imbued bars to finish the quest.<br><br>a bbk might not be considered a &quot;good&quot; weapon these days, but for someone starting out clean on a new server it's gonna serve you well. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22361 target="shemm">Shemm Tankdamob</a><br>54 Champion of <a href=http://fantasy.limefusion.com </a>Fantasy<br><img src="http://users.surfanytime.co.uk/brian.yeo/shemm.JPG" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http